<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>纽约时报 &amp;gt; 美国 &amp;gt; 政治</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/spotlight/on-politics</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Wed, 11 Mar 2026 22:26:48 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>一些民主党人已经在考虑南卡罗来纳州 2028 年的初选</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/03/11/us/politics/south-carolina-primary-democrats-2028.html</link><description>该州 2028 年的初选可能很重要，并且已经引起了一些民主党人的关注。</description><pubDate>Wed, 11 Mar 2026 22:26:48 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/03/11/us/politics/south-carolina-primary-democrats-2028.html</guid></item><item><title>民主党关注经济，伊朗战争给中期选举蒙上阴影</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/03/09/us/politics/iran-war-midterm-election-economy.html</link><description>民主党人专注于经济，而共和党人希望他们专注于经济。</description><pubDate>Mon, 09 Mar 2026 22:12:04 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/03/09/us/politics/iran-war-midterm-election-economy.html</guid></item><item><title>塔拉里科的社交媒体论文线索、就业报告和更多政治新闻</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/03/06/us/politics/talarico-social-media-democrats-jobs-report.html</link><description>对于一些民主党人来说，世代更迭伴随着令人尴尬的社交媒体过去。</description><pubDate>Fri, 06 Mar 2026 22:49:43 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/03/06/us/politics/talarico-social-media-democrats-jobs-report.html</guid></item><item><title>特朗普领导下的德克萨斯州下一步会怎样？ 4 个大问题。</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/03/04/us/politics/trump-texas-paxton-talarico-house-runoff.html</link><description>最直接的问题是：特朗普会做什么？</description><pubDate>Wed, 04 Mar 2026 23:31:51 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/03/04/us/politics/trump-texas-paxton-talarico-house-runoff.html</guid></item><item><title>这些民主党人能让 2028 年选举出现好斗的中间派吗？</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/03/02/us/politics/democrats-centrism-2028-election.html</link><description>温和的民主党倡导团体和智库“第三条道路”制定了一项庞大且昂贵的计划来塑造 2028 年总统竞选。</description><pubDate>Tue, 03 Mar 2026 01:34:27 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/03/02/us/politics/democrats-centrism-2028-election.html</guid></item><item><title>读者对即将到来的德克萨斯州初选的评价</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/02/27/us/politics/texas-elections-senate-primary.html</link><description>我们在该州的读者提供了了解当前政治世界中心的窗口。</description><pubDate>Fri, 27 Feb 2026 23:42:54 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/02/27/us/politics/texas-elections-senate-primary.html</guid></item><item><title>社交媒体如何塑造特朗普的国情咨文演讲</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/02/25/us/politics/trump-sotu-social-media-reactions.html</link><description>以下是社交媒体如何塑造您对国情咨文的印象。</description><pubDate>Thu, 26 Feb 2026 00:45:27 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/02/25/us/politics/trump-sotu-social-media-reactions.html</guid></item><item><title>关于特朗普国情咨文演讲的五个重大政治问题</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/02/23/us/politics/trump-speech-state-of-union-questions.html</link><description>关税、生活成本、移民：总统在重大问题上采取谨慎的路线。</description><pubDate>Mon, 23 Feb 2026 23:31:43 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/02/23/us/politics/trump-speech-state-of-union-questions.html</guid></item><item><title>人工智能将在 2026 年中期选举中亮相</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/02/20/us/politics/ai-midterms-elections.html</link><description>我们的科技专栏作家 Kevin Roose 解释了人工智能的潜在影响。</description><pubDate>Fri, 20 Feb 2026 22:52:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/02/20/us/politics/ai-midterms-elections.html</guid></item><item><title>随着参议院初选提前投票开始，德克萨斯州选举季升温</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/02/18/us/politics/texas-elections-senate-primary.html</link><description>两党的参议院初选正在紧锣密鼓地进行。</description><pubDate>Wed, 18 Feb 2026 23:06:57 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/02/18/us/politics/texas-elections-senate-primary.html</guid></item></channel></rss>